user_review: I was pleasantly impressed by the superior quality of the sandwiches and pork buns...WOW! And the smell just makes you immediately want to devour the entire thing on the spot! Right now, they are having a student special, which comprises of a sandwich and a soda for only $5.00! It REALLY doesn't get better than that!Also very conveniently located near UQAM metro.Keep it up guys!

Dreaming of those banh mi sandwiches and bao buns I had a few weeks ago @banhmiexpress_mtl  I've tried quite a few banh mi places in Montreal and this place is by farrrr the best! They're bread is unbeatable - so fresh , fluffy and crispy and not too chewy like some other places I've been to. Service was excellent and each dish was delicious ! I highly recommend if you're in the plateau area but it's also worth the detour if you're not!! Can't wait to come back for more. Not expensive at all paid about 40$ for two and was more than stuffed.

They serve delicious banh mi, comforting pho, fresh spring rolls and others.. but they also launched new products! I tried the Nem spring rolls with fried egg inside (MY FAV' it's so crunchy and the flavour is ) and the fried ice cream (For those who loves sweets stuff like me, this dessert was really good )
By far the best spot for pho we have found in montreal! Nothing is better on a cold night and the price is right too. Tried it out once and now it's one of our regular spots!

Yummy! Banh Mi Express was served to the artists at a benefit I was part of. We had the pork buns and were impressed by the quality. All ingredients were super fresh and the sandwiches were bursting with flavour. Delicious!
Super amazing banh mi sandwich! Quality a+. They catered at an event for us and everyone couldn't stop talking about these sandwiches!
